dot_zsh Repository Version History
==================================

v26.02 (Release Date: TBD)
--------------------------
- Prevent zsh nomatch errors when /opt is empty by using local nullglob and directory check.
- Integrate erase_history into sysadmin scripts environment.

v26.01 (2026-01-30)
-------------------
- Remove single-letter global pipe aliases to prevent unintended command expansion.

v25.10 (2025-10-24)
-------------------
- Remove unused chmod from command dependency check in install_dotzsh.sh.
- Standardize all shell scripts by removing trailing exit status lines (exit $?) for POSIX-safe reuse.
- Add alias mm to run cltmp before mail.
- Add jjj, kkk and mmm aliases for combined clear cd cltmp and mail workflow.

v25.08 (2025-08-20)
-------------------
- Add --uninstall option for installer to remove all installed components.
- Add alias mapping from m to mail in alias list.
- Add alias h for last 30 history entries and change his to show last 50.

v25.07 (2025-07-22)
-------------------
- Standardize shell script comments to start with verbs instead of using 'Function to' phrasing.
- Move usage instructions above version history and improve section structure in installer script.

v25.06 (2025-06-26)
-------------------
- Update installer scripts to display full header block as help message.
- Improve installer script reliability by explicitly returning exit codes in main functions.

v25.04 (2025-04-29)
-------------------
- Improved install_dotzsh.sh by adding strict error checking for filesystem operations.
- Unified log output format by introducing [INFO] and [ERROR] tags.

v25.03.1 (2025-03-28)
---------------------
- Set initial window title to zsh in screen or tmux environments.

v25.03 (2025-03-23)
-------------------
- Major overhaul of installation scripts.
- Fine-tuned alias configurations.
- Adjusted HISTSIZE and SAVEHIST to 10000 for better performance.
- Switched the repository license from LGPLv3 to a dual license under GPLv3 or LGPLv3, and updated related documentation.

v25.02 (2025-02-25)
-------------------
- Major refactoring and ensured POSIX compliance.
- Improved maintainability and modularity of scripts.
- Enhanced error handling and logging mechanisms.
- Standardized environment setup for better compatibility.

v11.12 (2011-12-31)
-------------------
- First official release.

First Commit (2011-05-24)
-------------------------
- Commemorating the first commit and push, marking the inception of the project.
